<%# `?` keyboard-guide overlay (R10) -- Increment 0 shipped only the open/close plumbing
    (a bare toggle proving the mode-dispatch foundation); this increment (the closeout,
    "Increment 6") replaces that stub with the full bindings reference: every binding
    shipped across R3-R8 (NORMAL navigation/theme/mode-switches/hint-jump), Esc, and the
    COMMAND registry's v1 command list.

    The NORMAL-mode/mode-switch table below is hand-authored -- those bindings are a fixed
    switch-statement in keyboard_nav_controller.js, not data in a JS structure to source
    from. The COMMAND-registry list is the opposite: data-keyboard-nav-target=
    "guideCommandList" is an EMPTY <dl> container that
    keyboard_nav_controller.js#renderGuideCommandList() populates directly from
    app/javascript/keyboard_nav/commands.js's COMMAND_REGISTRY at connect() -- a single
    source of truth, not a hand-duplicated copy that could silently drift the day P1.9
    adds a metrics-query command (it will appear here automatically, no ERB change
    required).

    Native <dialog>: the one deliberate focus-trap exception in this feature (R11) -- it
    gives focus-containment, Esc-to-close, and ::backdrop semantics from the browser for
    free, which is exactly right for a full "here are the bindings" help panel.
    COMMAND/SEARCH stay plain, non-trapping bars, deliberately not <dialog>s.
    aria-labelledby points at the heading below (WAI-ARIA APG dialog pattern) so screen
    readers announce "Keyboard bindings, dialog" on open, not just "dialog." No custom
    open/close transition is applied anywhere in this partial, so there is nothing for
    R11's prefers-reduced-motion bullet to gate here -- .showModal()/.close() are already
    instant, same as every other keyboard-nav UI element (status line, command/search bar,
    hint badges). %>
<dialog
  id="keyboard-guide-dialog"
  data-keyboard-nav-target="guideDialog"
  aria-labelledby="keyboard-guide-dialog-title"
  class="font-mono backdrop:bg-black/50 rounded-box p-6 max-w-lg w-[90vw] text-base-content bg-base-100"
>
  <h2 id="keyboard-guide-dialog-title" class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Keyboard bindings</h2>

  <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 mb-3">
    Default <strong>NORMAL</strong> mode, from a hardware keyboard:
  </p>
  <dl class="text-sm mb-5 grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3 gap-y-1.5 items-baseline">
    <dt><kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">h</kbd> <kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">j</kbd> <kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">k</kbd> <kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">l</kbd></dt>
    <dd>Scroll left / down / up / right</dd>

    <dt><kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">g</kbd> <kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">g</kbd></dt>
    <dd>Scroll to top</dd>

    <dt><kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">G</kbd></dt>
    <dd>Scroll to bottom</dd>

    <dt><kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">g</kbd> + <kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">h</kbd>/<kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">w</kbd>/<kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">p</kbd>/<kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">l</kbd></dt>
    <dd>Jump to home / writing / projects / lab (lab has no page yet)</dd>

    <dt><kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">t</kbd></dt>
    <dd>Cycle theme</dd>

    <dt><kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">f</kbd></dt>
    <dd>Hint-jump -- label every on-screen link; type its label to open it</dd>

    <dt><kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">:</kbd></dt>
    <dd>Enter COMMAND mode</dd>

    <dt><kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">/</kbd></dt>
    <dd>Enter SEARCH mode -- <kbd class="kbd kbd-xs">n</kbd>/<kbd class="kbd kbd-xs">N</kbd> steps through results, Enter opens the highlighted one</dd>

    <dt><kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">?</kbd></dt>
    <dd>Toggle this guide</dd>

    <dt><kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">Esc</kbd></dt>
    <dd>Return to NORMAL from any mode, or close this guide</dd>
  </dl>

  <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 mb-3">
    <strong>COMMAND</strong> mode (<kbd class="kbd kbd-sm">:</kbd>) -- v1 commands. The
    registry is extensible: future commands (e.g. metrics queries) appear below
    automatically once registered, no template change required.
  </p>
  <dl
    data-keyboard-nav-target="guideCommandList"
    aria-label="Command registry"
    class="text-sm mb-6 grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3 gap-y-1 items-baseline"
  ></dl>

  <form method="dialog">
    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-sm">Close</button>
  </form>
</dialog>
